1. Calculate the number of pens and pencils that can be bought using the formula: (total - cost1 - cost2) / (cost1 / cost2)
2. Calculate the factorial of the number of pens and pencils using the factorial function.
3. Multiply the factorial of the number of pens and pencils by the factorial of cost1 and cost2 to get the total number of ways to buy pens and pencils.

The time complexity is O(1) because the factorial function has a constant time complexity. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the function calls. The energy implications are low because the solution involves simple mathematical calculations and does not consume significant energy.

